		<h5>
			Inheritance
		</h5>
		<p>
		In object-oriented programming, inheritance allows one class to see and use the methods and properties of another class.
		</p>
		<ul>
			<li>
				<p>Based on <b>DRY</b> : Don't Repeat Yourself principal</p>
			</li>
			<li>
				<p>Whenever there is <b>X is-a Y</b> relationship, there's a good chance that we should be using inheritance.
			</li>
		</ul>
		<p>To achieve inheritance, we use <code>prototype</code></p>
		<h6>Syntax</h6>
<pre>
function Animal(){
	//some code
}

function Penguin(){
	//some code
}

Penguin.prototype = new Animal();
</pre>
		<p>All the properties/methods of <code>Animal</code> are now available to <code>Penguin</code> through prototype.</p>
